base.!doc:
Converts a number into a text representation with the given radix (base).
@param {number} number The number that you want to convert. Must be an integer greater than or equal to 0 and less than 2^53.
@param {number} radix The base radix that you want to convert the number into. Must be an integer greater than or equal to 2 and less than or equal to 36.
@param {number} [min_length] The minimum length of the returned string. Must be an integer greater than or equal to 0.
@returns {string} Number that is the text representation with the given radix (base).
@see For further information, see &nbsp;{@link https://docs.oasis-open.org/office/OpenDocument/v1.3/cs02/part4-formula/OpenDocument-v1.3-cs02-part4-formula.html#BASE | docs.oasis-open.org}
@example rosetta.base(7, 2); // returns '111'
@example rosetta.base(15,2,10); // returns '0000001111'

begins.!doc:
Determines whether a particular substring is stored at the beginning of another string.

This function is case-sensitive. If the either parameter is a list, the function tests each element
of the second parameter against each element of the first parameter and returns true if any match occurs.

@param {string} within_text Any string.
@param {string} find_text The string you want to search for at the beginning of string.
@returns {boolean} true if substring is contained within string, beginning from the first letter.
Returns false if not. This function is case-sensitive. If the either parameter is a list,
the function tests each element of the second parameter against each element of the first parameter
and returns true if any match occurs.
@see For further information, see &nbsp;{@link https://help.hcltechsw.com/dom_designer/14.0.0/basic/H_BEGINS.html|www.hcltechsw.com}
@example rosettajs.Text.begins('Miriam-McGovern','Miriam');  // returns true
@example rosettajs.Text.begins('Miriam-McGovern',['Abc','Miri']);  // returns true
@example rosettajs.Text.begins(['John Jones','Mary Hill'],['Mi', 'Pa']);  // returns false;

besselI.!doc:
Returns the modified Bessel function In(x).
@param {number} x The value at which to evaluate the function
@param {number} order The order of the Bessel function. If order is not an integer, it is truncated
@returns {number} The calculated modified Bessel function for the given value of x and the specified order
@see For further information, see &nbsp;{@link https://docs.oasis-open.org/office/OpenDocument/v1.3/cs02/part4-formula/OpenDocument-v1.3-cs02-part4-formula.html#BESSELI | docs.oasis-open.org}
@example rosettajs.besselI(2.6, 1) // returns 2.7553843378955585

besselJ.!doc:
Returns the Bessel function Jn(x).
@param {number} x The value at which to evaluate the function
@param {number} order The order of the Bessel function. If order is not an integer, it is truncated
