the cumulative distribution function, which is the probability that there are at most number_s successes; if FALSE, it returns the
probability mass function, which is the probability that there are number_s successes.
@returns {number} the individual term binomial distribution probability as number or an error if the arguments are incorrect.
@see For futher information, see&nbsp;{@link https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/binom-dist-function-c5ae37b6-f39c-4be2-94c2-509a1480770c | support.microsoft.com}

